# Why transmissions keep clutch and brakeseparate

Real transmissions distinguish them clearly.

| Component  | Connects                          | Example       |
| ---------- | --------------------------------- | ------------- |
| **Clutch** | rotating member ↔ rotating member | sun ↔ carrier |
| **Brake**  | rotating member ↔ housing         | ring ↔ case   |

Examples in real gearboxes:

* **4L60E**

  * Forward clutch
  * Reverse clutch
  * Low band (brake)

* **ZF 8HP**

  * C1 clutch
  * C2 clutch
  * B1 brake
  * B2 brake

Engineers always model them separately.

